<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,588,1224]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,588,613]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Color pattern as in 
<taxonomicName box="[494,623,589,613]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="percarus">
<emphasis box="[494,623,589,613]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">A. percarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but basal blue area on pronotum more greenish, darker blue area in elytral depressions larger and extending to humeri and somewhat posteriorad, posterior 
<number box="[1093,1107,624,648]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[1116,1128,624,648]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="3.0">3</number>
of elytra golden green with golden setae, black beneath with greenish reflections in male and coppery reflections on dorsal portion of metacoxal plate and abdominal ventrites, patches of silvery setae on lateral portions of abdominal ventrites 
<number box="[1318,1363,696,720]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
. Front dark bluish-green in male, red in female, with strong medial depression with few short silvery setae on lower 
<number box="[1393,1403,732,756]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1414,1430,732,756]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="2.0">2</number>
, epistoma very narrow, less than 
<number box="[516,526,768,792]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[536,552,768,792]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="4.0">4</number>
width between antennal insertions; pronotum with strong prehumeral carinae, deep, nearly circular medial depression for 
<number box="[636,646,804,828]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[656,671,804,828]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="2.0">2</number>
width of pronotum along base and strong lateral depressions behind middle; apices of elytra broadly rounded or rounded-truncate with few coarse teeth; prosternum of male nearly glabrous, femora with small teeth on ventral margins; male with metatarsomere 
<number box="[1035,1049,876,900]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="1.0">1</number>
shorter than 
<number box="[1201,1243,876,900]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
combined. Male genitalia as in Fig. 
<number box="[365,396,912,936]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="58.0">58</number>
.
</paragraph>
