<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,588,1224]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1092,1117]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Discussion.</emphasis>
This species was originally described from a unique female. Superficially it looks very similar in coloration to 
<taxonomicName box="[300,488,1129,1153]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="percarus">
<emphasis box="[300,488,1129,1153]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Agrilus percarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but is probably not closely related to it. 
<taxonomicName box="[939,1128,1129,1153]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rossanae">
<emphasis box="[939,1128,1129,1153]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Agrilus rossanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs most conspicuously from 
<taxonomicName box="[212,341,1165,1189]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="percarus">
<emphasis box="[212,341,1165,1189]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">A. percarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the others in this species group in having strong prehumeral carinae and a deep round depression across the midline on the basal 
<number box="[556,566,1200,1224]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[576,592,1200,1224]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" value="2.0">2</number>
of the pronotum. The male is 
<quantity box="[931,1019,1200,1224]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.4" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="5.4">5.4 mm</quantity>
, the female 
<quantity box="[1154,1244,1200,1224]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
